    <h2>Why Recycling Matters</h2>
    <p>
      Recycling helps reduce the amount of waste,
      saves natural resources, and cuts down on pollution from making 
      new products.
    </p>

    <h3>Common Recyclable Materials</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Paper &amp; Cardboard</strong> – newspapers, boxes, office paper.</li>
      <li><strong>Plastic</strong> – bottles and containers with recycling symbols.</li>
      <li><strong>Glass</strong> – bottles and jars (usually rinsed first).</li>
      <li><strong>Metal</strong> – drink cans and food tins.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Simple Recycling Tips</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Check local recycling rules on your council or city website.</li>
      <li>Rinse containers to remove food and liquid.</li>
      <li>Flatten cardboard boxes to save space.</li>
      <li>Avoid putting plastic bags or dirty items in the recycling bin.</li>
    </ol>

    <p>
      When in doubt, check before you throw it out. 
    </p>
	
